{"article_id":"Qm8UbiY3yw6rGDqe","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Congress Will Vote On Keystone XL Pipeline , With An Eye On Louisiana","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Two bills","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"that would authorize building the controversial Keystone XL pipeline","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"will soon come to a vote in Congress ,","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"as their sponsors","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"- Sen. Mary Landrieu , D-La. , and Rep. Bill Cassidy , R-La . -","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"head toward a runoff election next month","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"to decide","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"who will win the Senate race .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"`` On the Senate floor , Landrieu called for action on the Canada-to-Texas pipeline project ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"saying ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"' I believe","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"with a push we could actually get the votes","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that we need to pass the Keystone pipeline . ' ``","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Soon after , Republican leaders in the House scheduled a vote Thursday on a Keystone bill","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"sponsored by Landrieu 's rival , Cassidy .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"`` The two face off in a Dec. 6 runoff .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The pipeline is a key issue in Louisiana ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"where the oil and gas industry dominates . ''","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Energy company TransCanada 's Keystone XL pipeline would carry tar sands oil from Canada to Texas ;","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"it has been a polarizing issue ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"pitting those","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"who say","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"it would create thousands of jobs","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"against environmentalists","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"who say","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"tar sands oil is too expensive and toxic","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"to refine .","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"Where one side says","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"the plan would bolster the energy industry ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"the other says","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"it would increase greenhouse gases .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Wary landowners along its path have also spoken out ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"complaining","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"that the pipeline would disrupt their property","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and damage farms","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"- particularly if it ever sprang a leak .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"As the Two-Way has reported ,","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"`` In February , a Nebraska judge struck down a 2012 law","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"that allowed part of the pipeline to run through the state . ''","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"The AP notes","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"that the Obama administration is n't welcoming news of a vote on the matter :","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"`` While the White House stopped short of directly threatening a veto ,","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"spokesman Josh Earnest said","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"President Barack Obama takes a 'dim view ' of legislative efforts","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to force action on the project .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Earnest reiterated Obama 's preference","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"for evaluating the pipeline through a long-stalled State Department review . ''","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":95,"left":0,"right":94,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":55,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":55,"left":50,"right":54,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":50,"left":49,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":49,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":54,"left":51,"right":53,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":51,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":53,"left":6,"right":52,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":